Coronavirus guidance is being updated.
Read the Prime Minister’s statement for the latest information.

There are currently limited commercial options to available to return to the UK from French Overseas Territories.
Flights between mainland France and French overseas territories are formally suspended. However, there are limited flights from Réunion (Saint Denis Airport) to mainland France (Paris Charles de Gaulle airport) with Air Austral and Air France. Please check with your airline for the latest information.
You will need to pay for your return travel to the UK. If departure options are available but you cannot afford the travel costs and have exhausted all other options for getting funds, you may be eligible to apply for an emergency loan from the government. This is a last resort option and you would need to repay the loan when you are back in the UK. For more information, you should contact Corporate Travel Management (CTM). CTM are a commercial partner of the FCO and are authorised to administer such loans on behalf of the FCO.
Travel to departure point
To travel within or to transit through French Overseas Territories, you should complete an attestation de déplacement dérogatoire to certify your reason for travel. You can carry a physical copy or an electronic version of this “attestation” (declaration). This declaration should be completed before starting your journey.
Travel via mainland France
If you are travelling via mainland France, you will need to complete a separate travel certificate. See travel advice for France.
If you are returning to France from a coronavirus affected area the French authorities have issued advice in English
Arrival in the UK
When you arrive back in the UK, follow the guidance for when you return to the UK on steps you should take to protect yourself and others.
